What's the difference between a tool and a regular Component?
-------------------------------------------------------------

A component or set of components in a session are 
instruments that need to be synchronized and maintain a 
sequential data flow. You can't suddenly rewind the 
Global Clock to analyze better a moment. On the other 
hand, a quantitative tool can make many requests for 
different time periods, useful for flexible tools that 
require time periods instead of purely sequential data.